item.title: Ipmuted myself?
item.dc:creator: @Coelho Coelho
item.description:
@Coelho wrote:

[quote=“ForTheThrills, post:5, topic:401460”]Go to your source files and search a file

then click it and your name should be there, delete it.[/quote]
What if your server is using mysql?
What if your server is running on linux and the filesystem is case sensitive?
What if someone named the file differently?
What if the ipmutes are kept in serializable class outputted file?
What if… What if… /whatif

ontopic: Try doing what ForTheThrills said. If you don’t know what it is its probably delta or pi. If it isn’t, well…
